parameters: This table is fill of the MC's immediate wealth which
is in a dwindling supply, causing the MC to only want
to use this for an emergency, like say, paying for an
expensive medicine for a serpent that drags a boat?
Some of the clothing found in the temple that the MC
has discovered is enchanted to resist age, leading her
to believe that it's the clothing used for religious
rituals. The armor on the other hand she assumes is from...
the priests of this temple to defend it against monsters
and elemental beasts. She can't use any of it tho since
she's trained with daggers, and the pregnancy doesn't work
with the armor or the robes since they're both tight fitting.
Believe me, she's tried :P
Some of the random trinkets that the MC's managed to find
while digging. She's currently working on cleaning all of them
and wants to submit everything to the museum of history in the
south. She'll make a guess as to what everything is used for.
Dirt that the MC has had to remove from the temple. She
wants nothing more than to completly unbury the temple, but
is well aware that would take years away from her being able
to study other ruins and stuff.
Documentation of everything she's found here as well
as order fourms and maps of this contenent. She even does some
of her duties as a princess from here, although she'll just
call it annoying work that gets in the way of history.
Need I explain why a history nerd has so many books?
While her main focus is history, MC knows that she needs
no keep herself alive in order to be able to study said
history, so she keeps this garden well tended, often spending
the last few moments of her day tending to everything.
Stockpile of foods that won't go bad if not used for a while.
Boxes that will be filled with all the things she finds
while uncovering this temple, everything in here to be shipped
to the museum of history so it can be preserved better.
Despite appearences, MC does have a friend who comes over
every so often, much to MC's annoyance due to the risk of
monsters attacking her friend during their travels. Friend
is just making sure that MC doesn't die from lack of anything.
If MC brings in excess dirt into the temple, she'd never
forgive herself for ruining the sanctanty of the place,
so she takes a bath at least once a day, sometimes 2 depending
on her activities on that given day.
A pit to make charcoal for writing. Not really how charcoal
is made irl, but I want to show MC's inginuity and thinking
skills to realize that she'll run out of ink eventually, and
so decides to make charcoal to write with instead.
